Abstract: The title of first American baby of the millennium had not been officially decided shortly after midnight today, but locally, a brand new Queens native is making her bid.    The girl, 7 pounds 8 ounces, was born two seconds after midnight at Elmhurst Hospital Center in Queens, said Dario Centorcelli, a hospital spokesman. He did not know the girl's name.
